@NODE 1. "Introduction"

Hi!   This  is  my  first  program  on the Aminet.  It's based on an AMOS
program done by a friend of mine, Paulo Marques Figueira.  I've made some
@{"improvements" Link 4.}  on it, so I called this version "ZEUS IIe".  The "e" stands
for "English", as the original version was in Portuguese.

I hope you like this program!  8^)

@ENDNODE

@NODE 2. "What is ZEUS?"

ZEUS  is  an  impressive  program that will amaze people, specially those
that don't know how a computer works, like:

            - Your girlfriend
            - Your parents
            - Your relatives
            - PC users

It  will  answer virtually ANY question, as it is the ultimate artificial
intelligence software.

How does it do that?  It's simple, see @{"How to use it" Link 3.}.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 3. "How to use it"

ZEUS  is pretty simple.  By running this program, it will open a standard
Amiga  screen and window, and will prompt you for a question.  Don't type
the question yet.  Type the answer (limited to 30 characters).  While you
type  the  answer, the program will show an introduction to the question,
like:   "My  first question is this one:".  People won't pay attention to
what  you  are  typing,  because  they will be looking at the screen.  So
they'll think you're typing that introduction.

If  your  answer  ends  before  the  introduction, press "/" (slash), and
continue  typing anything until the end of this (introductions always end
with ":" (colon)).

Just  after  the  colon,  start  typing the question corresponding to the
answer  you  just typed.  The question is limited to 45 characters.  This
question will be typed normally on the screen.

Press  <Return>  when  you  finish  typing the question and...  ZEUS will
answer it, and your friends will believe it!!!

Repeat  this  procedure  until the fifth question, or close the window to
quit the program.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 4. "Improvements"

The following improvements were done to the original program (by Paulo
Marques Figueira):

- It multitasks well.

- Implementation of the "/" to end the answer.

- Implementation of the 5 questions limit, thus avoiding that the
  introductions start repeating.

- The executable file is smaller, and crunched with PowerPacker (by Nico
  Francois)

- Runs on WB or CLI, and doesn't need IconX.

- It uses Intuition, and not that ugly AMOS screen.

@ENDNODE

@NODE 5. "Bugs"

Yes, there are some bugs on the program. I want to remove them on future
version but, in the meanwhile, let me tell you who they are:

- After the 45th character of the question, the letter just go "out of
  the screen"

- No correction allowed.  So, avoid typos!  8^)

- (add the bugs you've found here)

@ENDNODE

